      "author": "jcig789",
      "description": "  Release Notes — Ledgr v0.1.8\r\n\r\n  Mobile UX overhaul, currency symbols, bottom navigation, and bug fixes.\r\n\r\n  **Navigation**\r\n  - New bottom navigation bar with active state indicators (top border, background tint, weight bump)\r\n  -  Add button redesigned as a bordered square — distinct from navigation tabs\r\n  - \"Log\" renamed to \"Add\" throughout\r\n  - Settings button now uses a gear icon instead of text\r\n\r\n  **Currency**\r\n  - Currency symbols displayed everywhere: $, ¥, ₱, € instead of USD/JPY/PHP codes\r\n  - 50+ currencies supported in the symbol map\r\n  - Default currency changed to USD for new installs\r\n  - Adding/removing currencies now instantly refreshes all open views\r\n\r\n  **Mobile fixes**\r\n  - Summary cards display in 2-column grid on mobile\r\n  - Action buttons right-aligned, currency toggles left-aligned\r\n  - Cash flow statement shows all 4 columns with compressed layout\r\n  - Net Worth edit mode uses card layout — balance field always visible\r\n\r\n  **Net Worth**\r\n  - Add Account opens an inline form with name, currency, and type selector\r\n  - Account type (bank/ewallet/cash/credit) selectable at creation\r\n  - Investment Accounts table header fixed\r\n\r\n  **Charts**\r\n  - Savings rate gauge rebuilt using circular ring — no more arc math bugs\r\n  - Gauge colors: green (≥20%), amber (10–19%), red (<10%)\r\n  - Gauge value centered inside ring",
